db -> delete from the cursor’s starting position to the beginning of the word.

daw -> easily remembered by the mnemonic delete a word. It doesn’t
just remove the word, it also deletes a whitespace character. 

Making effective use of the dot command often requires some forethought. If
you notice that you have to make the same small change in a handful of
places, you can attempt to compose your changes in such a way that they
can be repeated with the dot command.
